&lt;p&gt;One of our Direct clients is looking to add a Seasoned Sr Business Systems Consultant to their team, to support in-flight system development (custom build) and enhancement projects, complete contracting / pre-SLC assessments for new projects, assess new business capability requests and coordinate technical teams to deliver the capabilities. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Initiate and Plan Project:
	&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with business and IT management to establish project goals, objectives, financials, and deliverables.
	&lt;li&gt;Build and manage the project plan, resources, and Gantt charts to accomplish the project scope.
	&lt;li&gt;Project Control and Quality Management:
	&lt;li&gt;Evaluate scope changes, issues, and risks, working with stakeholders to resolve them.
	&lt;li&gt;Measure performance against the original plan and budget, ensuring compliance with corporate and functional policies and procedures.
	&lt;li&gt;Maintain and update the RAID log to track project risks, actions, and issues.
	&lt;li&gt;Execute and Close Project:
	&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute work plans, securing authorized resources to complete all activities.
	&lt;li&gt;Lead the team in delivering the project scope, gather lessons learned, and obtain final project approval.
	&lt;li&gt;Assist in managing the process to ensure all validation deliverables are completed.
	&lt;li&gt;Project Communication:
	&lt;li&gt;Produce and distribute project reports to provide accurate status and decision support to stakeholders.
	&lt;li&gt;Make recommendations to resolve issues and manage risks based on the current project status.
	&lt;li&gt;Resource and Team Management:
	&lt;li&gt;Coordinate and assign resources to ensure project needs are met, effectively assign tasks based on team members’ abilities.
	&lt;li&gt;Motivate the project team to achieve desired outcomes.
	&lt;li&gt;Decisions and Financial Control:
	&lt;li&gt;Make decisions impacting project-level activities; influence or have authority over the project budget.
	&lt;li&gt;Develop and manage a financial plan, maintaining spend within +/- 10% of the overall budget.
	&lt;li&gt;Track and update financials in Clarity, coordinating estimates and invoices with vendors.
	&lt;li&gt;Vendor Coordination:
	&lt;li&gt;Coordinate vendor activities and ensure timely milestone delivery.
	&lt;li&gt;Ensure vendor purchase orders (POs) are processed promptly.
	&lt;li&gt;Project Meetings:
	&lt;li&gt;Facilitate Project Management meetings to oversee execution activities with IT System Owner and Principal Business Systems Consultant.
