&lt;br&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;
The State of Michigan is seeking an experienced and dynamic Senior Project Manager to lead complex, large-scale IT initiatives. This role requires a strong blend of project management expertise, leadership capabilities, technical awareness, and change management proficiency to ensure successful project outcomes aligned with business objectives and enterprise standards.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Provide strategic oversight, leadership, and accountability for one or more large, complex IT projects, typically lasting longer than 6 months, involving 20 or more team members, and requiring executive-level communication and coordination.
	&lt;li&gt;Ensure alignment with State of Michigan project management methodologies, including SUITE, investment management, and systems engineering methodology.
	&lt;li&gt;Lead cross-functional teams through all phases of project planning and execution, including the development of integrated schedules, risk management plans, and budget tracking.
	&lt;li&gt;Monitor and report on project progress regarding scope, quality, schedule, and budget, and escalate issues and risks to executive leadership as necessary.
	&lt;li&gt;Perform long-term release planning to support organizational strategic goals and ensure alignment with broader enterprise initiatives.
	&lt;li&gt;Evaluate technical requirements in collaboration with IT and business stakeholders, proposing solutions that meet business needs while adhering to SOM best practices and industry standards.
	&lt;li&gt;Apply structured change management practices grounded in the ADKAR (Prosci) framework to ensure stakeholder alignment and successful adoption of project deliverables.
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Technical Competencies:&lt;/strong&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Strong knowledge of APIs, system interfaces, and multi-system integrations across complex IT environments.
	&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of IT infrastructure components and their interactions within networked environments (e.g., firewalls, VIPs, F5 listeners, ports).
	&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with core infrastructure environments including networks, servers, storage, web platforms, and virtual/cloud solutions.
	&lt;li&gt;Ability to effectively collaborate with technical teams and external vendors to support solution design, integration, deployment, and issue resolution.
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Change Management and Stakeholder Engagement:&lt;/strong&gt; This position plays a critical role in driving change adoption through:

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Integration of change management principles from the outset of the project.
	&lt;li&gt;Close collaboration with stakeholder engagement leads to develop and implement communication plans, facilitate training sessions, and monitor organizational readiness.
	&lt;li&gt;Supporting stakeholders at every level to reduce resistance, align expectations, and ensure long-term user adoption of new systems and processes.
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Ideal Candidate Profile:&lt;/strong&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to lead large, cross-functional teams and manage high-visibility projects with medium to high risk.
	&lt;li&gt;Strong leadership, interpersonal, and communication skills with experience interacting with Agency Leadership.
	&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage both technical delivery and change management efforts within complex environments.
	&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated success managing vendor-supported projects with integrated technical components and stakeholder groups.
&lt;/ul&gt;

